Hoc Latinis proprie est imbuere, quia tum vasa illa imbuebant vino, quod Diis libabant. Inde postea imbuere de omnibus rebus, quae primo usui nostro accomodantur. Ca- tullus de Argo nave. ² Semper infinita, insatiabilis, neque copia, neque inoffici, &c.] See Perizon. on Sanct. 4, e. 7, n. 2, who defends this reading against Mem-sius and Carolus on Gellius 3, 1.—C.

³ Recepta republica, &c.] The reader, in order to understand what Sallust here intends, must know that Marius and his party had got the management of public affairs into their hands. This Sulla wrested from them by force of arms, which is the thing meant by the words recepta republica. And his conduct thus far was good and laudable„ and approved by our author as such, in the words bonis initiis.
